# Cursor Project Rules

- Always use a data-driven, DB-first development approach.
- Always read documentation in `\web\Senlysh` and existing rules before developing or suggesting anything.
- Always review Supabase database state (tables, relationships, RLS policies, functions, triggers, migrations) before developing or suggesting changes.
- Always run TypeScript and lint error tests, then build before production deployment. If any code changes are made, use Browser MCP to test the build locally before deploying to production.


